Axtel, Bimbo, Elektra, HRT, Vale: Latin America Equity Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-02-25T06:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/axtel-bimbo-elektra-hrt-vale-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The MSCI Latin America Index snapped a three-day slump,
rising 0.1 percent to 4,409.59.  Brazil    HRT Participacoes em Petroleo SA  (HRTP3 BS): The Brazilian
oil and gas company that raised about $1.5 billion in an initial
offering last year agreed to buy UNX Energy Corp. for about 1.3
billion reais ($780 million) to expand in  Namibia . The stock
dropped 3.2 percent to 1,839.99 reais.    Vale SA  (VALE5 BS): The world’s biggest iron-ore exporter
said fourth-quarter profit almost quadrupled to $5.92 billion.
Vale shares were unchanged at 49.25 reais.    Mexico   Axtel SAB (AXTELCPO MM): Mexico’s second-largest land-line
phone company reported a net loss of 92.8 million pesos ($7.6
million) in the fourth quarter. Axtel slipped 0.1 percent to
6.95 pesos.  Cia. Minera Autlan SAB (AUTLANB MM): The manganese producer
reported net income of 56.7 million pesos in the fourth quarter.
The stock fell 0.8 percent to 34.75 pesos.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA* MM): The retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas  said net
income fell to 2.12 billion pesos in the fourth quarter. Elektra
rose 0.5 percent to 504.26 pesos.  Grupo Bimbo SAB (BIMBOA MM): The world’s largest bread
maker reported fourth-quarter profit of 1.37 billion pesos.
Bimbo fell 2.2 percent to 93.89 pesos.  Grupo Comercial Chedraui SA (CHDRAUIB MM): The supermarket
chain based in Xalapa, Mexico, reported net income of 341.6
million pesos in the fourth quarter. The stock gained 0.4
percent to 37.98 pesos.  Megacable Holdings SAB (MEGACPO MM): Mexico’s largest cable
carrier said net income fell to 552 million pesos in the fourth
quarter. The stock fell 2.3 percent to 27.39 pesos.  TV Azteca SAB (TVAZTCPO MM): Mexico’s second-largest
broadcast television network said net income rose to 1.39
billion pesos in the fourth quarter. Azteca dropped 1.7 percent
to 8.28 pesos.    Peru   Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SA (BVN PE): Peru’s biggest
precious-metals producer said fourth-quarter profit rose to a
record $222.8 million. The stock fell 0.7 percent to $45.70.  To contact the reporter on this story:
